▸ video_prompt（English only — motion description for Kling/Seedance video AI）
  - Describe camera motion, environmental/scene dynamics, AND character movement actions.
  - NO visual appearance descriptions (no face, hair color, eye color, clothing, body features — these are handled by reference images). ONLY describe what characters DO and HOW they move.
  - CONTINUITY OPENING (required for shot_no ≥ 2): The first sentence of video_prompt MUST begin with a continuity clause referencing the previous shot's ending state: camera angle handoff, character position, or scene momentum. Example: "Continuing from the wide establishing shot, camera pushes in slowly as [character name] turns..." or "Picking up where the previous close-up ended, pulling back to reveal..."
  - MINIMUM LENGTH: At least 100 English words.
  - Core principle: describe EVERY element's motion individually and specifically. Keyword lists forbidden.
    Generic phrases like "fluid motion" or "dynamic atmosphere" add nothing — describe actual physics.
  - Required motion layers (all applicable layers must be present):
    A. Camera: exact movement type matching camera_type + speed qualifier
       static → "locked-off with organic micro-stabilization, imperceptible ±0.3px breathing drift"
       push   → "slow cinematic dolly-push at 0.2x speed, closing distance by ~30% over shot duration"
       pan    → "smooth leftward pan at 15°/sec, horizon line held steady throughout"
       pull   → "steady dolly-pull at 0.15x speed, environment expanding outward from center"
       crane_up → "slow vertical crane rise at 0.1m/sec, horizon line descending in frame"
    A2. Character actions (required if characters appear in this shot): use exact character name from 【角色信息】; describe actions ONLY, no appearance
       — Always lead with the character's exact name, then describe what they do within the shot duration
       ✅ "Ling Yun walks slowly toward the stone gate at frame center, each step deliberate and heavy, advancing roughly 30% across frame over shot duration"
       ✅ "Bai Xue on the left turns upper body 60° rightward, arms falling naturally to sides"
       ✅ "Ling Yun enters from right edge at urgent pace, halts at center, weight shifting backward"
       ❌ "handsome young man swings sword" → use character name, write "Ling Yun swings sword"
       ❌ "white-robed woman turns around" → use character name, write "Bai Xue turns slowly around"
       ❌ "figure at frame center walks..." → replace "figure" with the character's actual name
    B. Atmospheric particles: every particle type in the scene gets its own motion clause
       — dust motes: "fine dust motes suspended in [light shaft zone], drifting diagonally [direction] at
         0.4cm/sec, each mote spending 2-3 seconds in lit zone before exiting frame edge"
       — smoke/fog: "thin ground-level mist at 10-20cm height drifting [direction] at 0.2cm/sec, density
         [thickening/thinning] 15% over shot duration, thickest at [location]"
       — embers/sparks: "embers rising from [source] at 0.6m/sec with slight rightward drift, each spark
         brightening 30% at peak then fading over 0.4s as it cools"
       — rain: "rain falling diagonally at 70° from upper-right, 4m/sec, fine density, impacting [surface]
         with 2-3mm splash rings spreading outward and dissipating in 0.3s"
    C. Foliage, fabric, and flexible objects:
       — each named plant/object: "oscillating [amplitude in degrees] at [frequency Hz] from [wind/air source],
         returning with slight overshoot oscillation of [decay duration]s"
       — fabric on surfaces (banners, canopies, cloth): direction of billow, amplitude, frequency
    D. Liquid and fire dynamics (if present):
       — water: flow direction, speed, surface disturbance frequency, reflection change
       — fire/torches: flicker rhythm (Hz), intensity variance (%), color shift at base vs. tip
       — steam/mist: rise rate, dispersion radius, opacity change per second
    E. Structural and ground settling (subtle environment physics):
       — dust particles displaced from surfaces: dislodgment trigger, roll distance, settling location
       — loose debris: vibration amplitude, caused by what (wind / ground tremor / distant impact)
       — shadow edge migration if light source is moving or flickering
    F. Lighting dynamics: how light changes within the shot duration
       — intensity ramp: "[brightening/dimming] ~[X]% over shot duration"
       — color temperature shift: "warming [from X to Y]K over shot duration"
       — shadow edge movement: "shadow boundary migrates [direction] at [rate]cm/sec"
    G. Temporal arc: how the shot's emotional energy evolves through environment alone
       — describe what changes from first frame to last that conveys emotional shift
       — ✅ "opens on static stillness — only the light dimming and shadow deepening signal time's passage,
           each falling dust mote amplifying the weight of the emptied space"
       — ❌ "tense atmosphere" → vague, AI invents arbitrary motion
  - Example (locked-off, empty ruined courtyard after battle):
    "Locked-off camera with subtle organic stabilization, imperceptible breathing drift of ±0.3px;
    foreground cracked flagstone surface: three small pebble fragments vibrate ±1mm from low-frequency
    distant rumble, fine grit rolling 1-2cm into nearby crevices over the shot duration; mid-ground
    stone pillar fracture edge: thin trickle of mortar dust falls in a 15cm stream from the break point
    at irregular 2-4 second intervals, each stream lasting 0.3s then ceasing; background pine canopy:
    branches oscillating 6° at 0.4Hz from residual wind, recovering with 0.8s damped overshoot; torch
    bracket flame left-of-center: flickering at 3Hz with 20% intensity variance, tip color cycling
    between orange-yellow and cooler amber, casting a 1.5Hz shadow-edge oscillation across the adjacent
    stone wall; suspended torch smoke rising vertically at 0.3cm/sec, bending 8° rightward at 1.5m
    height where corridor draft catches it, dispersing into haze above 2m; ambient dust motes in torch
    light shaft drift diagonally downward at 0.5cm/sec, each visible for 2-3 seconds; overcast sky
    layer holds motionless; cold grey diffuse top-light dims ~12% over shot duration, shadows
    deepening without directional shift; emotional arc: opens on suspended aftermath stillness, the
    only motion being the relentless physical decay — dust falling, flame guttering, shadow thickening —
    until silence itself becomes suffocating by frame-close"

